                        <h4>About me</h4>
                        <p>It was in 1999 when I "built" my first website. It was kind of crappy, built with a WYSIWYG-Editor and it only worked in Internet Explorer. A few years later I came to a place called "c-base" (the people who run this place pretend to build a crashed space station, some of them might really believe it) and there I met some cool guys who really knew how to build a website. One of them showed me the German HTML-Reference project <a href="http://www.selfhtml.org" target="_blank" class="ext">selfhtml.org</a>. 'If you want to build a website, learn this', he said. So I did and so it came that I fell in love with code.</p>
                        <p>I had spent some years with learning and practicing HTML and CSS on W3C standards, when I deceided to make my passion a profession. After a 2 years retraining as digital media designer I started my own business together with my husband. We had a little advertising agency. In this I was responsible for Webdesign and Webdevelopment while my husband took care for grafic design and video and animation.</p>
                        <p>After almost 9 years things went a little worse in our business but something new was about to occur: at DCI ... <i>[To be continued...]</i></p>
